Email Customers in Salesforce Classic

Cases generated via Email-to-Case or On-Demand Email-to-Case display in an Emails related list. The first 77 characters of an email message appear in the related list so that you can see what the message is about without having to click on it.

Send and Reply to Email in the Salesforce Classic Case Feed
Use features to save time when writing messages and customize emails.
Add Images and Files to Email Messages
Give customers comprehensive information by attaching files and add inline images.
Use Email Templates
Ensure consistency, save time, and include basic information with one click.
Work with Draft Emails
Save messages without sending them immediately and create approval processes for email messages.

Review and Approve Email Drafts in the Salesforce Classic Case Feed
Review and approve messages written by agents before they are sent to customers.

Customize Emails with the Rich Text Editor
Format text, add bulleted or numbered lists, and add images and links.
